@using PKFAuditManagement.ViewModels
@model QC7FormCreationViewModel

<div class="justify-content-center">
    <main id="main" class="main">
        <div class="pagetitle">
            <h1>Form QC7(3)</h1>
        </div><!-- End Page Title -->
        <section class="section">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-12">
                    <form asp-action="SubmitQC7Form" asp-controller="QC7Form" method="post">
                        @if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(Model.ErrorMessage))
                        {
                            <div class="alert alert-danger">
                                @Model.ErrorMessage
                            </div>
                        }
                        @if (ViewBag.Errors != null)
                        {
                            <ul>
                                @foreach (var error in ViewBag.Errors)
                                {
                                    <li>@error.ErrorMessage</li>
                                }
                            </ul>
                        }
                        else if (ViewBag.ErrorMessage != null)
                        {
                            <span class="alert alert-danger">@ViewBag.ErrorMessage</span>
                        }
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h5 class="card-title">Continuing engagement / client evaluation checklist</h5>
                                <span class="text-danger">* indicates a mandatory field</span>
                                <br><br>
                                <form>
                                    @Html.AntiForgeryToken()
                                    <div class="row mb-3">
                                        <label asp-for="Client" class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Client:<span class="text-danger"> *</span></label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <input type="text" class="form-control" asp-for="Client">
                                            <span asp-validation-for="Client" class="text-danger"></span>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="row mb-3">
                                        <label for="inputEmail3" class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Period Ended:<span class="text-danger"> *</span></label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <input type="date" class="form-control" asp-for="PeriodEnded">
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="row mb-3">
                                        <label asp-for="EngagementType" class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Type of Engagement:<span class="text-danger"> *</span></label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <input type="text" class="form-control" asp-for="EngagementType">
                                            <span asp-validation-for="EngagementType" class="text-danger"></span>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="row mb-3">
                                        <div class="col-sm-2">
                                            <strong>Prepared by:<span class="text-danger"> *</span></strong>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="col">
                                            <input type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Signature" asp-for="PreparedBy">
                                            <span asp-validation-for="PreparedBy" class="text-danger"></span>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="col">
                                            <input type="date" class="form-control" asp-for="PreparedByDate" value="@DateTime.Today.ToString("yyyy-MM-dd")">
                                            <span asp-validation-for="PreparedByDate" class="text-danger"></span>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="row">
                                        <div class="col-sm-2">
                                            <strong>Reviewed by:<span class="text-danger"> *</span></strong>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="col">
                                            <input type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Signature" asp-for="ReviewedBy">
                                            <span asp-validation-for="ReviewedBy" class="text-danger"></span>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="col">
                                            <input type="date" class="form-control" asp-for="ReviewedByDate" value="@DateTime.Today.ToString("yyyy-MM-dd")">
                                            <span asp-validation-for="ReviewedByDate" class="text-danger"></span>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <br>
                                    <hr class="my-4">
                                    <div class="row mb-3">
                                        <label class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Prior year’s fee<span class="text-danger"> *</span></label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <span class="input-group-text">$</span>
                                            <input type="number" class="form-control" asp-for="PriorYearFee" placeholder="0.00" id="comp1">
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="row mb-3">
                                        <label class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Time Costs<span class="text-danger"> *</span></label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <span class="input-group-text">$</span>
                                            <input type="number" class="form-control" asp-for="TimeCosts" placeholder="0.00" id="timeCosts">
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="row mb-3">
                                        <label class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Prior year’s recovery rate (Net fee / time costs)<span class="text-danger"> *</span></label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <input type="number" class="form-control" disabled placeholder="0.00" id="PriorYearRecoveryRate">
                                            <span class="input-group-text">%</span>
                                            <input type="hidden" asp-for="PriorYearRecoveryRate" id="PriorYearRecoveryRateHidden">
                                        </div>
                                    </div>

                                    <div class="row mb-3">
                                        <label class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Any outstanding unpaid audit fees?<span class="text-danger"> *</span></label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" id="gridCheck1" asp-for="AnyOutstandingUnpaidAuditFees">
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="row mb-3">
                                        <label class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Type of activities of client<span class="text-danger"> *</span> </label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <input type="text" class="form-control" asp-for="TypeOfClientActivities">
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="row mb-3">
                                        <label class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Risk rating in prior year<span class="text-danger"> *</span></label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <input type="text" class="form-control" asp-for="RiskRatingPriorYear">
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="row mb-3">
                                        <label class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Any Suspicious Transaction Report filed with CAD in prior year(s)?<span class="text-danger"> *</span></label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" onchange="toggleSuspiciousTransactionReportPriorYear()" id="suspiciousTransactionReportPriorYearCheckbox" asp-for="AnySuspiciousTransactionReportFiled">
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="row mb-3" id="suspiciousTransactionReportPriorYearRow" style="display: none;">
                                        <label class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Comment for Suspicious Transaction Report filed</label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <textarea class="form-control" asp-for="SuspiciousTransactionReportFiledComment" id="suspiciousTransactionReportFiledComment"></textarea>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="row mb-3">
                                        <label class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Name of safeguard reviewer (if applicable)</label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <input type="text" class="form-control" asp-for="SafeguardReviewerName">
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="row mb-3">
                                        <label class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Non-audit fees charged for this client (tax, accounting, secretarial, XBRL etc)<span class="text-danger"> *</span></label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <span class="input-group-text">$</span>
                                            <input type="text" class="form-control">
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="row mb-3">
                                        <label class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Any outstanding unpaid non-audit fees?<span class="text-danger"> *</span></label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" id="gridCheck1" asp-for="AnyOutstandingUnpaidNonAuditFees">
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="row mb-3">
                                        <label class="col-sm-2 col-form-label" data-bs-toggle="tooltip" data-bs-placement="bottom" title="To calculate before providing non-audit services (“NAS”) to disclose promptly to TCWG if the 50% threshold is crossed.
                                                Computed as % of NAS from client and its controlled entities (excluding ARS fees) over fees from audit of the financial statements from client and its controlled entities.">
                                            <span class="link-text">Fee concentration (Non-audit services fees / audit fees = x%)<span class="text-danger"> *</span></span>
                                        </label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <input type="text" class="form-control" asp-for="FeeConcentration" placeholder="0.00">
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="row mb-3">
                                        <label class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Proposed fee for current year<span class="text-danger"> *</span></label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <span class="input-group-text">$</span>
                                            <input type="number" class="form-control" asp-for="ProposedFeeCurrentYear" placeholder="0.00">
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="row mb-3">
                                        <label class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Budgeted Time Cost<span class="text-danger"> *</span></label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <span class="input-group-text">$</span>
                                            <input type="number" class="form-control" asp-for="BudgetedTimeCost" placeholder="0.00" id="budgetedTimeCost">
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="row mb-3">
                                        <label class="col-sm-2 col-form-label" data-bs-toggle="tooltip" data-bs-placement="bottom" title="Should at least be 30%.
                                            And to disclose reasons for continuance if the recovery rate is below 30%.">
                                            <span class="link-text">Proposed recovery rate for current year</span>
                                        </label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <input type="number" class="form-control" disabled id="proposedRecoveryRateCurrentYear" placeholder="0.00">
                                            <input type="hidden" asp-for="ProposedRecoveryRateCurrentYear" id="proposedRecoveryRateCurrentYearHidden">
                                            <span class="input-group-text">%</span>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="row mb-3">
                                        <label class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Public Interest Entity (PIE)?<span class="text-danger"> *</span></label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" id="pieCheckbox" onchange="toggleRiskLevel()" asp-for="IsPublicInterestEntity">
                                        </div>
                                    </div>

                                    <div class="row mb-3" id="riskLevelRow" style="display:none;">
                                        <label class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Type of PIE</label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <select class="form-control" id="riskLevel" asp-for="PublicInterestEntityType">
                                                <option value="" selected>Select an option</option>
                                                <option value="Listed">Listed</option>
                                                <option value="Financial Institution">Financial Institution</option>
                                                <option value="Large Charity">Large Charity</option>
                                                <option value="Large Institution of Public Character (“IPC”)">Large Institution of Public Character (“IPC”)</option>
                                            </select>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>

                                    <div class="row mb-3">
                                        <label class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Is this a transnational entity (TNE)?<span class="text-danger"> *</span></label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" id="gridCheck1" asp-for="TransnationalEntity">
                                        </div>
                                    </div>

                                    <div class="row mb-3 align-items-center">
                                        <label class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">If this is a transnational audit (TNA)?<span class="text-danger"> *</span></label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <input class="form-check-input me-3" onchange="toggleTransnationalAuditRow()" type="checkbox" id="transnationalAuditCheckbox" asp-for="TransnationalAudit">
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="row mb-3" id="transnationalAuditRow" style="display: none;">
                                        <label for="inputEmail3" class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">
                                            Comments for Transnational Audit
                                        </label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <textarea class="form-control" id="transnationalAuditComment" rows="4" asp-for="TransnationalAuditComment"></textarea>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>

                                </form>

                                <!-- QC7SubForms Beginning -->
                                @foreach (var subForm in Model.SubForms)
                                {
                                    <input type="hidden" name="SubForms.Index" value="@subForm.QC7SubFormID" />
                                    <h5 class="card-title">@subForm.SubFormType</h5>
                                    <div class="table-responsive">
                                        <table class="table table-bordered table-striped">
                                            <thead class="table-light" style="background-color: #f8f9fa;">
                                                <tr>
                                                    <th class="text-left pl-3 text-uppercase" style="width: 50%;">Objectives and detailed tests</th>
                                                    <th class="text-left text-uppercase">Ref</th>
                                                    <th class="text-left text-uppercase">Sign</th>
                                                    <th class="text-left text-uppercase">Date</th>
                                                    <th class="text-left text-uppercase">Ref/Comment</th>
                                                </tr>
                                            </thead>
                                            <tbody>
                                                @foreach (var objective in subForm.Objectives)
                                                {
                                                    <input type="hidden" name="SubForms[@subForm.QC7SubFormID].Objectives.Index" value="@objective.QC7FormObjectiveID" />

                                                    <tr class="font-weight-bold" style="background-color: #f8f9fa;">
                                                        <td colspan="5"><b>@objective.Objective</b></td>
                                                    </tr>
                                                    @foreach (var testDescription in objective.TestDescriptions)
                                                    {
                                                        <input type="hidden" name="SubForms[@subForm.QC7SubFormID].Objectives[@objective.QC7FormObjectiveID].TestDescriptions.Index" value="@testDescription.QC7FormTestDescriptionID" />
                                                        <tr class="text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-400">
                                                            <td>
                                                                <div>
                                                                    <p>@Html.Raw(@testDescription.Description)</p>
                                                                </div>
                                                            </td>
                                                            <td>
                                                                <input type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Ref" name="SubForms[@subForm.QC7SubFormID].Objectives[@objective.QC7FormObjectiveID].TestDescriptions[@testDescription.QC7FormTestDescriptionID].Reference" />
                                                            </td>
                                                            <td>
                                                                <input type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Signed By" name="SubForms[@subForm.QC7SubFormID].Objectives[@objective.QC7FormObjectiveID].TestDescriptions[@testDescription.QC7FormTestDescriptionID].SignBy" />
                                                            </td>
                                                            <td>
                                                                <input type="date" class="form-control" value="@DateTime.Today.ToString("yyyy-MM-dd")" name="SubForms[@subForm.QC7SubFormID].Objectives[@objective.QC7FormObjectiveID].TestDescriptions[@testDescription.QC7FormTestDescriptionID].SignDate" />
                                                            </td>
                                                            <td>
                                                                <input type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Ref/Comment" name="SubForms[@subForm.QC7SubFormID].Objectives[@objective.QC7FormObjectiveID].TestDescriptions[@testDescription.QC7FormTestDescriptionID].Comment" />
                                                            </td>
                                                        </tr>
                                                    }
                                                }
                                            </tbody>
                                        </table>
                                    </div>
                                }
                                <h5 class="card-title">Conclusion</h5>
                                <div class="row mb-3">
                                    <label for="inputEmail3" class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">
                                        Based on the above information, are there any risks associated with the proposed work? <span class="text-danger"> *</span>
                                        <br>
                                        If No: Accept engagement with no safeguard required.
                                        <br>
                                        If Yes, there is risk:
                                        <br>
                                        (a)	Explain what is the risk in current year compared to prior year
                                        <br>
                                        (b)	Are there any safeguards that should be applied? Yes / No
                                        <br>
                                        (c)	Specify the nature of the safeguard to address the issue(s) identified in the evaluation of continuance of engagement or client
                                        <br>
                                    </label>
                                    <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                        <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" id="risksAssociatedCheckbox" onchange="toggleRisksAssociated()" asp-for="AnyRiskAssociated">
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div id="risksAssociatedRow" style="display:none;">
                                    <div class="row mb-3">
                                        <label for="inputPassword3" class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">(a) Explain what is the risk in current year compared to prior year:</label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <textarea class="form-control" rows="4" asp-for="RiskExplanationCurrentYearPriorYear" id="riskExplanationCurrentYearPriorYear"></textarea>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="row mb-3">
                                        <label for="inputPassword3" class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">(b)	Are there any safeguards that should be applied?</label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" id="isSafeguardApplied" asp-for="IsSafeguardApplied">
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="row mb-3">
                                        <label for="inputPassword3" class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">(c)	Specify the nature of the safeguard to address the issue(s) identified in the evaluation of continuance of engagement or client: </label>
                                        <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                            <input type="text" class="form-control" asp-for="NatureOfSafeguard" id="natureOfSafeguard">
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="row mb-3">
                                    <label for="inputEmail3" class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Continuing engagement / client *risk rated in current year as:<span class="text-danger"> *</span>  <br> *See <a>Appendix 1</a> for categories of risks</label>
                                    <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                        <select class="form-control" id="riskLevel" asp-for="ContinuingEngagementRiskRated">
                                            <option value="Normal (N)">Normal (N)</option>
                                            <option value="Moderate (M)">Moderate (M)</option>
                                            <option value="High Risk (H1)">High Risk (H1)</option>
                                            <option value="High Risk 2 (H2)">High Risk 2 (H2)</option>
                                        </select>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="row mb-3">
                                    <label for="inputEmail3" class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Safeguard review partner assigned (if applicable): </label>
                                    <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                        <input type="text" class="form-control" id="inputText" asp-for="SafeguardReviewPartnerAssigned">
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="row mb-3">
                                    <label for="inputPassword3" class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">
                                        Is there any suspicious transaction report (“STR”) to be filed with CAD based on the above evaluation?<span class="text-danger"> *</span> <br><br>
                                        <i><u>Note</u><br>If yes, please set out the rationale and basis for STR in a separate memo. If in doubt, please discuss with the firm’s Money Laundering Reporting Officer (MLRO) and if necessary, seek advice from legal counsel after discussing with Managing Partner and /or Quality Management Partner.</i><br>
                                    </label>
                                    <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                        <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" id="isSuspiciousTransactionReportFiled" onchange="toggleSuspiciousTransactionReport()" asp-for="IsSuspiciousTransactionReportFiled">
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="row mb-3" id="strRationale" style="display:none;">
                                    <label for="inputPassword3" class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">
                                        Rationale and Basis for STR
                                    </label>
                                    <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                        <textarea class="form-control" id="strRationaleComment" rows="4" asp-for="SuspiciousTransactionReportFiledRationale"></textarea>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="row mb-3">
                                    <label for="inputEmail3" class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Should engagement or client be retained or rejected?<span class="text-danger"> *</span> </label>
                                    <div class="col-sm-10 d-flex align-items-center">
                                        <select class="form-control" id="riskLevel" asp-for="EngagementRetainedRejected">
                                            <option value="Retained">Retained</option>
                                            <option value="Rejected">Rejected</option>
                                        </select>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="row mb-3">
                                    <div class="col-sm-6">
                                        <label for="inputPassword3" class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Prepared by:<span class="text-danger"> *</span></label>
                                        <input type="text" class="form-control" id="inputText" placeholder="Engagement Manager" asp-for="EMPreparedBy">
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="col-sm-6">
                                        <label for="inputPassword3" class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Date:<span class="text-danger"> *</span></label>
                                        <input type="date" class="form-control" id="inputText" asp-for="EMPreparedByDate">
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="row mb-3">
                                    <div class="col-sm-6">
                                        <label for="inputPassword3" class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Approved by:<span class="text-danger"> *</span></label>
                                        <input type="text" class="form-control" id="inputText" asp-for="EPHODApprovedBy" placeholder="Engagement Partner / Head of Division">
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="col-sm-6">
                                        <label for="inputPassword3" class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Date:<span class="text-danger"> *</span></label>
                                        <input type="date" class="form-control" id="inputText" asp-for="EPHODApprovedByDate">
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="row mb-3">
                                    <div class="col-sm-6">
                                        <label for="inputPassword3" class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Final Approval by:<span class="text-danger"> *</span></label>
                                        <input type="text" class="form-control" asp-for="MPHODQMPApprovedBy" id="inputText" placeholder="Managing Partner / Head of Division / Quality Management Partner">
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="col-sm-6">
                                        <label for="inputPassword3" class="col-form-label">Date:<span class="text-danger"> *</span></label>
                                        <input type="date" class="form-control" id="inputText" asp-for="MPHODQMPApprovedByDate">
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <h5 class="card-title"><u><i>Note</i></u></h5>
                                <p>
                                    <i>
                                        To enable the authorized person to approve, the following are the minimum documentation required to be submitted together with this Form:-
                                        <br> &ensp;(a)	Company BizFile search (full search is not required for a newly incorporated company or a company that is dormant)
                                        <br> &ensp;(b)	Screening of directors and ultimate beneficial owners owning more than 25% of the ultimate holding company using LexisNexis
                                        <br> &ensp;(c)	Notes of meeting(s) or communications with the management of the prospective client or persons knowledgeable about the prospect or notes written in QC6(3)
                                        <br> &ensp;(d)	Financial information if available
                                        <br> &ensp;(e)	Google search to obtain any further information about the company and the directors (exclude nominee directors) that are running and managing the operations of the company.
                                        <br> &ensp;(f)	Further procedures to be carried out on AML and CTF <u>should there be indicators or suspicion of integrity issues identified from the above client due diligence checking</u> may include (i) ascertaining how the entity’s operation is funded including the source of funds (ii) country where source of funds are derived  (iii) purpose of funds flow and whether it is considered unusual (iv) finding out from management any investigations past or current by regulators and authorities on matters relating to tax evasion, corruption charges, terrorism financing, money laundering and any fraud and irregularities and (vi) any other procedures considered necessary by the approver.
                                    </i>
                                </p>
                                <div class="text-center">
                                    <button type="submit" class="mt-3 end-0 btn btn-primary">Submit QC7 Form</button>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </form>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        <section class="section">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-12">
                    <div class="card">
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h1 class="card-title">Appendix 1</h1>
                            <p>
                                <i>
                                    Extract (partial) from the Firm’s Quality Management Manual – Categories of Risk (paragraph 8.14 to 8.15)
                                    <br><br>
                                    The firm classifies its engagements into four categories namely: -
                                    <br><br>
                                    &nbsp;&nbsp;a)  High risk engagement requiring full scope review by the safeguard reviewer (H1)
                                    <br><br>
                                    &nbsp;&nbsp;b)  High risk engagement requiring focused review on the modified opinion or a specific area(s) by the safeguard reviewer (H2)
                                    <br><br>
                                    &nbsp;&nbsp;c)  Moderate risk engagement may require areas to be subjected to focused or selective review by safeguard reviewer based on engagement partner’s discretion (M)
                                    <br><br>
                                    &nbsp;&nbsp;d)  Normal risk engagement requiring no safeguard review (N)
                                    <br><br>
                                    A safeguard review is an objective evaluation of the significant judgements made by the engagement team and the conclusions reached in formulating the report before the report is issued. The firm typically requires safeguard reviews for all the following “high risk” engagements:
                                    <br><br>
                                    (A “high risk” client that is rated as H1, is a client considered to be of high public interest or likely to be subject to higher levels of scrutiny for a variety of reasons.)
                                    <br><br>
                                    &nbsp;&nbsp;1.	Transnational entities (which include some of the categories below) (Note it is only necessary to apply the safeguard review requirement for a subsidiary if it is greater than 15% of the group by turnover, gross assets or audit hours);
                                    <br><br>
                                    &nbsp;&nbsp;2.	Publicly traded or listed companies;
                                    <br><br>
                                    &nbsp;&nbsp;3.	Large charities with donation income of S$10 million or more;
                                    <br><br>
                                    &nbsp;&nbsp;4.	Other public interest entities, such as banks, financial institutions, insurance entities, large pension schemes, large publicly funded charities (with donation in excess of S$10 million), and regulated fund management activities including if their financial statements are likely to be used across national boundaries (i.e., internationally) or if they are important National Institutions;
                                    <br><br>a
                                    &nbsp;&nbsp;5.	“For sale” entities or those which are known to be targets for acquisition by another entity;
                                    <br><br>
                                    &nbsp;&nbsp;6.	Entities where a qualified audit report was issued in the last financial statements, or where a qualified audit report is expected to be issued in the current financial statements which is not due to a technical qualification such as those falling under H2;
                                    <br><br>
                                    &nbsp;&nbsp;7.	Entities where there are particular reporting difficulties where there may be doubts over the nature of audit report to be issued.
                                    <br><br>
                                    &nbsp;&nbsp;8.	First year audit of a new client arising from a change of auditors (unless the engagement is non-complex and straight-forward in nature which based on the engagement partner recommendation does not need a safeguard review).
                                    <br><br>
                                    &nbsp;&nbsp;9.	Any other significant concerns identified by the engagement partner that requires a safeguard review under H1.
                                    <br><br>
                                    The Firm classifies high risk engagements into two types namely H1 and H2.
                                    <br><br><br>
                                    <h3 class="card-title">H1 engagements</h3>
                                    For engagements such as those listed from (1) to (9) above, the firm classifies these engagements as High risk 1 (“H1”).
                                    <br><br>
                                    <h3 class="card-title">H2 engagements</h3>
                                    However, there are certain specific instances where the engagement is not really a “high risk” engagement simply because the entity incurred losses and has deficit in shareholder’s equity as the share capital is only S$2 and the funding is entirely by way of loans from the holding/related companies and there are no borrowings from third parties.  So long as the holding company provides the financial support and there is no risk of borrowings from third parties, there is no real risk of going concern. Thus, the modification of the audit report on going concern which is commonly the case with this type of engagement represents a technical modification and would not require a full scope review.
                                    Another specific instance would be the non-consolidation of a subsidiary by the Singapore holding company as the ultimate parent does not publish consolidated accounts that are publicly available. Again, this type of engagement is not really a high-risk engagement and the reason is commonly one of cost and benefit to the holding company which does not need the group accounts at the Singapore level.
                                    For those engagements as described above, they are classified as High risk 2 (“H2”). Such engagements will require only the modified opinion to be reviewed by the safeguard reviewer including the documentation of the matters that give rise to the modified opinion. Based on the judgement of the safeguard reviewer, he or she can extend the review to other areas on a selective basis as he or she deems necessary after discussion with the engagement partner or manager.
                                </i>
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
